    {
      "instruction": "<p>Reduce the heat to medium and add the <strong>chopped onion</strong>, <strong>sliced garlic</strong> and <strong>cornflour</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Add 400ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[520ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>with <strong>half</strong> your <strong>tamari soy sauce </strong>(you'll use the rest later!),<strong> ginger paste</strong>,<strong> hoisin sauce </strong>and<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and put the dish in the oven, uncovered, and cook for 20-25 min or until the sauce has thickened –<strong> </strong>this is your <strong>Chinese-style Fable mushroom</strong></p>",
